# DevSkyy Platform - .gitignore
#
# Reorganized/deduped 2026-07-09. Prior file had 6 exact-duplicate lines
# (.mypy_cache/, .ruff_cache/, *.log, logs/, htmlcov/, generated_3d_models/)
# plus ~10 functionally-redundant `**/x/` variants of already-recursive bare
# patterns (gitignore patterns with no leading slash already match at any
# depth — `**/foo/` adds nothing over `foo/`). Root cause: every entry was
# added reactively by whoever hit git-status noise that session, with no
# check against existing coverage. Same pattern nearly caused a real
# incident (see .claude/ section) when a whole engine + state dir went
# untracked and invisible in a worktree. No ignore behavior changes below
# except the .claude/ section (was blanket-ignored, now allow-listed).

# Ralph context file (persists across iterations, never commit deletions)
.ralph/ralph-context.md
.ralph/.ralph-context.bak
.ralph/ralph-loop.state.json

